^(?!/)(?!.*//)[a-zA-Z0-9]*\/[a-zA-Z0-9]+\/[a-zA-Z0-9]+(?<!/)$
(?!/) – Asserts the string does not start with a slash.

(?!.*//) – Asserts the string does not contain two slashes in a row (prevents consecutive slashes).

[a-zA-Z0-9]* – Matches any number of alphanumeric characters before the first slash.

\/ – Matches a single slash.

[a-zA-Z0-9]+ – At least one alphanumeric character between the two slashes.

\/ – Second slash.

[a-zA-Z0-9]+ – At least one alphanumeric character after the second slash.

(?<!/)$ – Asserts the string does not end with a slash.
